        "introduction": [
            {
                "titre": "Imagine this: Your engine starts smoking on the way home from watching the sunset in the mountains. You pull over and pop the hood, grabbing the small tool bag from your trunk. You are talking on the phone with the tow service, working with both hands to see what might have gone wrong with your engine, in the dark. You remember the flashlight you keep in your pocket for times like this, but how can you use it? You don't have a third hand, and you can't hold it in your mouth.",
                "sous_items": []
            },
            {
                "titre": "I experienced a situation very similar to that on a trip back from stargazing, and needless to say, it was not fun. If only I had a headlamp or some other way of securing the flashlight to my head, so I could see where I was working. That moment was the inspiration behind FlashClip, an easy way to convert a pocket flashlight into a head lamp, mounted on the brim of any-sized hat. In this Instructable, I will walk you through how I designed and built the first version of FlashClip, and how you can make one for yourself. Let's get started!",
                "sous_items": []
            }
        ],
