                            {
                                "titre": "With the clip done, I slid in my flashlight and mounted it on my baseball cap for a test. It worked super well! I could not shake it off of the brim, and the whole time the light was steady and didn't even shake in the clip. I tried two different configurations, one with the flashlight on the underside of the brim, and one with the flashlight ontop. I will say that the flashlight mounted under worked better for me because it was more stable, but if you're using a larger light, it might get in the way. I really love the way this project turned out, and now I have a helpful new addition to my preparation kit. I think this is a pretty handy little gadget, and I'm excited to see what the community thinks. I have included all of the files if you would like to print one for yourself, or make any adjustments. Thanks for reading!",
